Data Scientist		Optimal Strategix Group, Inc.		Atlanta or Philadelphia		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p></p><p><strong>Position Description </strong></p><p>The ideal candidate must have statistical, mathematical, predictive modeling as well as business strategy skills to build the algorithms necessary to ask the right questions and find the right answers. They also need to be able to communicate their findings, orally and visually. They must understand how the products are developed and even more important, as big data touches the privacy of consumers, they must have a set of ethical responsibilities. </p><p></p><p>The big data scientist must be able to program, preferably in different programming languages such as Python, R, Java, Ruby, Clojure, Matlab, Pig or SQL. The ideal candidate must have an understanding of No-SQL DBs such as Hadoop, Hive and/or MapReduce. In addition, the candidate must be familiar with disciplines such as: </p><p>• Natural Language Processing: the interactions between computers and humans; </p><p>• Machine learning: using computers to improve as well as develop algorithms; </p><p> Conceptual modeling: to be able to share and articulate modeling; </p><p>• Statistical analysis: to understand and work around possible limitations in models; </p><p>• Predictive modeling: most of the big data problems are towards being able to predict future outcomes; </p><p>• Hypothesis testing: being able to develop hypothesis and test them with careful experiments.</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p></p><p>Optimal Strategix Group (OSG) was founded in 2006 by Dr. Sukumar, a world renowned university professor and recognized expert in Marketing Strategy and Market Research. <br /><br />Leveraging proprietary approaches, enabling technologies, and advanced analytics, Dr. Sukumar and his associates have assisted clients in becoming more “customer centric” by providing differentiated, actionable insights into customer preferences and behaviors. Beyond the legacy of complex, primary research, OSG has added high value growth strategy, marketing strategy, and marketing/sales execution advisory services to it’s portfolio, in addition to mobile technologies and data analytics to capture multiple dimensions of the customer experience. <br /><br />Today, OSG has grown to over 100 associates with offices on the U.S., E.U., and Asia Pacific, including Customer Insights Centers of Excellence in Newtown, PA and Bangalore, India.</p></div>